{
  "stem": "27509.9",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think about the Shoah because when one is trying to understand [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] anything about life, and one is trying to understand the-- the-- the unshakable belief of the Jewish people in the God of Israel and so on, one can't help thinking about the Shoah.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One can't help asking questions, fundamental questions about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we all ask the same question.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Where was God in Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where was God in Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where was he?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Especially a religious person-- I-- I am not religious man, in the sense of orthodoxy, in a religious sense.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I am a man of-- of extraordinary-- a affinity of-- to the Jewish people, as a people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My understanding and my philosophy-- when I have created Bialik as-- as a sequence to my involvement with Scopus-- and I'm making that point to make myself understood-- I've explained that I am creating Bialik because at Scopus, Jewish culture is part of Jewish religion.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At Bialik, Jewish religion is part of the Jewish culture.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that is my affinity to my culture, to my people, to my past, to my future.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that is-- that was the driving force within me, both ideologically, philosophically, in terms of an historical analysis and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it remains so, to this day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And to that extent, one cannot-- how can one not think about-- one cannot-- you can't avoid.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the Holocaust is a companion of ours, and not only of ours.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Any thinking man-- there may be other people who may be more detached.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they can't avoid, if they are thinking and if they want to understand history in terms of a deeper perspective, or a more analytical retrospect.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
